{"questionId":"9076190","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A magnetized needle is oscillating on a string about a vertical axis in a horizontal magneticfield <em>B</em>. The time for 10 oscillations is recorded for different values of <em>B</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4692/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-11_om_06.15.15.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ1/01_01\"></p>\n<p>The graph shows the variation with <em>B </em>of the time for 10 oscillations together with the uncertainties in the time measurements. The uncertainty in <em>B </em>is negligible.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/5591afdb0430f77e717029a450ef6f0e768658dc.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the unit of <em>K</em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{s}}{{\\text{T}}^{\\frac{1}{2}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>s</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>T</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept </em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\\sqrt T \">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span><em>&nbsp;</em>or in words.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076190","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ1.1b.iii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the unit of K.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVer